# **Setting up git remote origin**

## **First, create your project folder on your computer and initialize a git repo**
1. mkdir "Project Folder Name"
2. cd "Project Folder Name"
3. git init
### **OR clone an already existing github repo**
1. mkdir "Project Folder Name"
2. cd "Project Folder Name"
3. git clone <repo-url>

## **Next,set remote origin within git repo if one doesn't exist**
1. git remote add origin <repo-url>
### **IF one exists and needs to be changed**
1. git remote set-url origin <repo-url>

## **Finally, to check whether the origin was set correctly use**
1. git remote -v
### **This will return all remotes listed in the repo**

